20 Whyalla Street is a prime retail property prominently located on the corner of Whyalla and Newcastle Street, opposite Bunnings Warehouse and DFO / Epi Centre in Fyshwick, Canberra's No.1 industrial / retail suburb.

The property sits on 3,356sqm block. Improvements were constructed in the 1960s and upgraded during the 1990s. The property comprises an L-shaped building with retail, office, storage and mezzanine level on the ground floor with an internal staircase leading down to a second retail area with adjoining offices and storage area.

Car parking is available on site for the minimum 41 vehicles as required by the Crown Lease, which is adequate taking into consideration the use of the building.

The entire property is leased to Sportsmans Warehouse expiring July 2014 with 3.5% annual increases.

For further information or to arrange an inspection, call the exclusive agent - Mark Nicholls, CB Richard Ellis.

12 Quilpie Crescent is an exciting new development situated on the Fringe of Fyshwick.  This location offers ease of access onto the Monaro Highway and Canberra Avenue making it an easy trip to the City CBD, Barton and a short drive to the Canberra Airport.  Various amenity is available around the building including various food and beverage offerings as well as public transport.

12 Quilpie Crescent offers two levels of high quality office accommodation, warehousing or a combination of both if required. First floor office spaces available at 298sqm*. The development features the following;

- High quality finishes
- Lift access
- Basement secure parking and generous on grade parking
- Excellent natural light and window coverage
- Combination of ground floor and first floor spaces available
- NBN ready

Integrated fit out options are available as well as full turn key solutions which can be discussed with the developers.

This is an excellent opportunity to occupy brand new office space at an affordable rate in a central location in Canberra.

Units 1 & 2 of 57-59 Kembla Street are 175sqm units of brick and steel construction suitable for retail, bulky goods or office use. They currently create a single unit of 350sqm with a minor partition separating the units.

They are offered for sale individually or in one-line.

The front unit offers a unique signage opportunity onto Kembla Street and strengthens the attraction to buy both units and retain some storage space at the rear.

12 car spaces and an awning along the side of the building make it easy for customers to access the units, a major attraction for retail operators in Canberra.

1 Albany street is a high profile site located on the corner of Albany Street and Collie Street in Canbeera's #1 commercial suburb - Fyshwick! The site comprises a clean and modern commercial building which was completed in 2005 with secure electronic gated access and security cameras.

A 445sqm high exposure office / showroom comprising:
- toilet facility
- store room
- security cameras
- wash bay with drain
- both roller door and swing door access
The unit is serviced by a 1,560sqm yard area with services such as water, air and electric.
This unit was previously occupied by Kennards Hire.

Albany Street is one of the main roads and thoroughfares in Canberra's largest industrial / commercial suburb, Fyshwick. 5-7 Albany Street is located approximately half way down Albany Street and provides high exposure and street presence. The block is also located within view of the junctions connecting Townsville Street and Collie Street.

An L-shaped showroom / warehouse building comprising an open plan retail area at the front serviced by sufficient on grade car parking. The building also comprises a storage area at the rear which has a mezzanine level accessed via stars on both sides. Located on the ground floor of the storage area are male and female toilet facilities, a kitchenette / lunch room and a shower.

The property is currently occupied by Oz Design Furniture, who has been in occupation of the building since the mid 1980's. The current lease is due to expire 30 June 2015 (end of 2014-2015 tax year) with 50% of outgoings recoverable from tenant. The tenant has shown no intention to vacate the property upon lease expiry.

The property boasts the flowing strengths and opportunities:
- Stand alone building on its own block (no body corporate / strata fees)
- Minimal maintenance
- Leased until 30 June 2015 with 50% of outgoings recoverable from tenant
- Same tenant has been in occupation since mid 1980's
- Opportunity to subdivide into 5 smaller tenancies
- Strong demand for small strata units and detached showroom/warehouses throughout Fyshwick

The property is for Sale by Expressions of Interest (EOI) closing Thursday 22 September 2011.

For further information or to arrange an inspection, please contact Mark Nicholls of CB Richard Ellis, Canberra.
